[{"sha":"860058301de30b6feedeb890f54f5475d26d82c7","author":{"name":"Alexander Belyaev","email":"a33a2701f6790f0a44360bcc1a194138e928e0d3@google.com"},"message":"[KERNEL_GEN] Add a separate bufferization pass for linalg.tiled_loop.

TiledLoopOp is generated only when a Linalg compute operation (linalg.generic,
linalg.dot, etc) is tiled. Due to a special structure of the resulting loop
nest we can make some assumptions about the operations in its body. For
example, that we don't have to allocate buffers for the `tensor.extract_slice`
if the source tensor is the block arg of the enclosing `linalg.tiled_loop`.

Bufferization of `tensor.insert_slice` inside of the tiled_loop also differs
from the conservative bufferization in the general case.

With the new pass we can still use bufferization patterns for LinalgOps from
MLIR Core for operations that are not in the body of the tiled_loop and use
custom bufferization patterns otherwise.
